 (IPA: [IPA: [kəˡmɔːɹəʊz]]), officially the Union of the Comoros ([French: Union des Comores], [IPA: [ynjɔ̃ de kɔmɔʀ]]; [Arabic: اتحاد القمر], [IPA: [ʔitːiˡħæːd ælˈqɒmær]], and until 2002 the Islamic Federal Republic of the Comoros), is a country in the Indian Ocean, situated at the northern end of the Mozambique Channel between northern Madagascar and northern Mozambique.
